a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes n k :: nat
assumes h0 : "n = 12"
and h1 : "k = 9"
shows  "n choose k = 220"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Compute $\dbinom{12}{9}$. The final Answer is 220
 ### Proof
 $\dbinom{12}{9}=\dbinom{12}{12-9}=\dbinom{12}{3}=\dfrac{12\times 11\times 10}{3\times 2\times 1}=\boxed{220}. $
 *)

theorem
fixes n k :: nat
assumes h0 : "n = 12"
and h1 : "k = 9"
shows  "n choose k = 220"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Find the value of ${12 \choose 9}$. The final answer is 220.
